<!-- Purpose: To test the SCRIPT element with the CHARSET attribute -->

<!-- Expected result: There are no actual results. The 'charset' attribute specifies to the browser that the character encoding of the linked document is 'ISO 8859-1' -->

<title>XHTML Functional -- SCRIPT - TYPE</title>

<script charset="ISO 8859-1" src="default.js"

type="text/javascript" language="javascript">

</script>

</head>

<body>

<p>This tests the CHARSET attribute of the the SCRIPT element. In

this case, the 'charset' attribute specifies to the browser that

the character encoding of the linked document is 'ISO 8859-1'. The

linked document is the 'script_charset.js' file which contains the

javascript function implemented below.<br />

<br />

Select a background color:<br />

</p>



<p><input type="button" value="blue"

onclick="changeBGColor('blue');" /> <input type="button"

value="green" onclick="changeBGColor('green');" /> <input

type="button" value="white"

onclick="changeBGColor('white');" /></p>

